“Task scheduler” broadly 3 tarah ka ho sakta hai:

1. CPU-style scheduler
        tasks, cooldown, priority, time slices
        LeetCode-type ya OS-flavored
2. Job scheduler
        run backup every day 2 AM
        cron, retries, dependencies
3. Distributed task scheduler
        queue + workers + retries + dead-letter + monitoring
        like Celery / Airflow-lite / Quartz-ish design

        Entities:
        Task, TaskRequest, Scheduler, TaskQueue, Worker, TaskHandler, TaskRepository, RetryPolicy

        Inputs:
        taskType, payload, scheduledTime, priority, retries, timeout, dependencies, recurrence

        Core APIs:
        submitTask()
        cancelTask()
        getTaskStatus()

        Flow:
        submit -> persist -> schedule -> dispatch -> execute -> update status -> retry/fail/success